        <!-- Book Description -->
        <div class="book-description">
            <h2>Description</h2>
            <p>In the quiet town of Willow Creek, nothing ever happens—until a shocking murder shatters the community's peace. The only witness to the crime is ten-year-old Lily, who hasn't spoken a word since the traumatic event.</p>
            
            <p>Detective Mark Harris, haunted by his own past failures, is assigned to the case. As he investigates, he discovers that Lily's silence holds the key to unraveling a web of secrets that powerful people in the town will do anything to protect.</p>
            
            <p>With time running out and threats closing in from all sides, Mark must find a way to communicate with Lily and uncover the truth before the killer strikes again. But can he earn her trust when she's too terrified to speak?</p>
            
            <p>Richardson masterfully weaves a tale of suspense, redemption, and the unbreakable bond between a damaged detective and a traumatized child. "The Silent Witness" will keep you guessing until the final, heart-stopping revelation.</p>
        </div>
        
